spirit:component.spirit:name: v_osd
spirit:component.spirit:description: The Xilinx On-Screen Display LogiCORE provides a flexible video processing block for alpha blending and compositing as well as simple text and graphics generation. Support for up to eight layers using a combination of external video inputs (from frame buffer) and internal graphics controllers (including text generators) is provided. Supported image sizes up to 4kx4k with YUVa 4:4:4 or 4:2:2 and RGBa image formats up to 1080p 60fps. The core is programmable through a comprehensive register interface for setting and controlling screen size, background color, layer position, and more using logic or a microprocessor. A comprehensive set of interrupt status bits is provided for processor monitoring. The LogiCORE is provided with two different interfaces: General Purpose Processor and EDK Pcore (including device driver).
